  "description": "The Asian Boyz (ABZ) are a Crip-affiliated street gang founded in the late 1980s in Long Beach, California to protect Cambodian refugees from the East Side Longos. They split from the Tiny Rascal Gang after an internal dispute. With 2,000-5,000 members in 28 cities across 14 states (FBI 2009), they are one of the largest Asian gangs in the US. Colors are blue/navy (West Coast) and green/black/white (Midwest/East Coast). Founder Marvin Mercado received 218 years for four murders. They have a long-running feud with the Wah Ching ('Summer Madness' shootouts in 1993). Some members serve in the US military and traffic drugs using that position.",
